Getter / setter for relative abundance data

relabundance.Rd

relabundance is a getter/setter for relative abundance stored in the assay slot ‘relabundance’ of a MicrobiomeExperiment object

relabundance(x, ...)

relabundance(x) <- value

relAbundanceCounts(x, abund_values = "counts", name = "relabundance")

# S4 method for SummarizedExperiment
relabundance(x)

# S4 method for SummarizedExperiment
relabundance(x) <- value

# S4 method for SummarizedExperiment
relAbundanceCounts(x, abund_values = "counts", name = "relabundance")

Arguments

x

a MicrobiomeExperiment object
...

optional arguments not used currently.
value

a matrix to store as the the ‘relabundance’ assay
abund_values

A single character value for selecting the assay to use for calculating the relative abundance.
name

A single character value for selecting the assay to stor the calculated relative abundance.

Value

For relabundance the matrix stored with the name “relabundance”. For relAbundanceCounts a modified x containing the relative abundances as an assay defined by name.

Examples

data(GlobalPatterns)
GlobalPatterns <- relAbundanceCounts(GlobalPatterns)
relabundance(GlobalPatterns)
